# Data Model Patterns

## Structure

```kotlin
@Serializable
data class TickerData(
    val symbol: String,
    val lastPrice: String,
    val priceChangePercent: String,
    val volume: String
)
```

## Rules

- Annotate all network/persistence models with `@Serializable`.
- Use `@SerialName("json_key")` when the JSON field name differs from the Kotlin property.
- Provide `null` or sensible defaults for optional fields: `val message: String? = null`.
- Keep models in the `model/` package — one file per logical group.
- Use `data class` for value types; regular `class` only when identity matters.

## Naming

- Model names match the domain concept: `TradingPair`, `OrderBook`, `NewsItem`.
- Navigation route models (e.g., `Market`, `CoinDetail`, `Favorites`, `Settings`) are `@Serializable` objects or data classes used with type-safe navigation.

## Navigation routes

```kotlin
@Serializable data object Market
@Serializable data object Favorites
@Serializable data object Settings
@Serializable data class CoinDetail(val symbol: String, val displaySymbol: String)
```

These are used directly as `composable<Market> { ... }` destinations in the `NavHost`.
